President Biden has declared a major disaster in North Dakota due to flooding from April 10 to May 6, 2023. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Funding will be available for emergency work, facility repairs, and hazard mitigation measures. Kenneth G. Clark of FEMA has been appointed to coordinate federal recovery operations. Further designations may be made in the future based on damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.